        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-03-21 23:43:39.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n> (1 comment)\n\nAh, I see.  However, that's just using the javax persistence API; it doesn't actually have any DB code for storing/retrieving, etc.",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "f1af8d7e6baa74f38b68ea7c0d4705d12f9581dc",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 477,
          "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
          "username": "jhh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-03-22 00:09:41.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nWhat bugs me is that all these dependencies that we could pick up silently.   Looking at all the other classes definition in this package, it seems to me that the class type of this field is very inconsistent with the rest.   Would you agree?",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "a639401693b2b5529ebf0278c6ba806958770d04",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 811,
          "name": "Jim Hahn",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jrh3@att.com",
          "username": "jrh3"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-03-22 00:40:32.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n> What bugs me is that all these dependencies that we could pick up\n > silently.   Looking at all the other classes definition in this\n > package, it seems to me that the class type of this field is very\n > inconsistent with the rest.   Would you agree?\n\nWith drools-pdp, for each DB table, we actually had two separate classes: one was a pure interface and the other was a JPA entity.  I wonder if we need the same thing here, only in this case we may actually want a third class, which is a pure POJO, with no JPA annotations.",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "8a08c59cfd5e1eb3f51b7d6e8c32d926761f3a29",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 57,
          "name": "Pamela Dragosh",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "pd1248@att.com",
          "username": "pdragosh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-03-22 00:46:03.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nI think this does a good job of removing duplicate classes. If dependencies become a problem, you could always do an exclusion of JPA from the modeling classes.",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
