      {
        "id": "f21b82d2a6450c881b6fc473af29dc2870c65c43",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2787,
          "name": "Liam Fallon",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "liam.fallon@est.tech",
          "username": "liamfallon"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-03-22 08:51:41.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 8:\n\nCan we discuss this at the standup? The idea of these concept classes is to avoid duplication of code and use common POJOs everywhere.\n\nIf we go down this road we will have duplicate classes for everything on the PDP side and we will have to write mapping code for all the classes, multiplying the code by 3 times.",
        "patchset_number": 8
      },
      {
        "id": "0eaaafb4bf12e1de3352d48a9d433b214020f99b",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3239,
          "name": "Ram Krishna Verma",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ramkrishna.verma@gmail.com",
          "username": "ramverma"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-03-22 11:13:15.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 8:\n\n(1 comment)",
        "patchset_number": 8
      },
      {
        "id": "fd79a17d7a0bcce45a035922d59816b1b173254c",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 477,
          "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
          "username": "jhh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-03-22 12:24:06.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 8:\n\nNote that serialization earlier using the concept key would render for the PolicyTypes supported:\n\n{ \n    key: \"blahblah\"\n    value: \"1.0.0\"\n}\n\nJust makes no sense to me ..",
        "patchset_number": 8
      },
      {
        "id": "404944343e92e1f0c5aa8b49c5845b8ec3e5309d",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 57,
          "name": "Pamela Dragosh",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "pd1248@att.com",
          "username": "pdragosh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-03-22 12:27:46.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 8:\n\nYes so perhaps we need to get a better understanding of the Concept Key classes and their role better. They seem to be the sticking point right now.",
        "patchset_number": 8
      },
      {
        "id": "13a3bdcdc7d4f192d28b9ea60dff327ae47fc2ed",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 477,
          "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
          "username": "jhh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-03-22 12:40:02.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 8:\n\nLiam, I guess I don't understand where the duplication comes from and I agree I it is better to avoid duplication.  I question though if a network protocol should be a model, requestIds, statistics reports, healthchecks, statuses, .. are not models and an API user should never be allowed to do anything with those.    I guess I need to understand how the duplication claim comes about.  I just see them as 2 different animals, if we are mixing the networking protocols with the user models, may be we are not doing something right.",
        "patchset_number": 8
      },
